LineNo: 12543315,

Narrator: As I turned my head to look out the...
en


As I turned my head to look out the window, I saw the lights at the palace gates go out.

LineNo: 12543425,

Narrator: That night, I couldn't sleep. Despi...
en


That night, I couldn't sleep. Despite a busy day, I wasn't feeling tired at all.

LineNo: 12543527,

Narrator: In the hope of clearing my mind, I...
en


In the hope of clearing my mind, I turned on the TV.

LineNo: 12543907,

Narrator: It was the Merkopan Cup Quarter Fin...
en


It was the Merkopan Cup Quarter Finals. An obscure Sordish team was playing in Arcasia against the football giants, Olympique Ventrie.

LineNo: 12544009,

Narrator: Before evening fell, I had received...
en


Before evening fell, I had received news of my sister-in-law's speech at the Alliance of Nations, openly threatening Sordland.

LineNo: 12544389,

Narrator: As her ally, I feared what conseque...
en


As her ally, I feared what consequences her actions would bring to Rizia.

LineNo: 12544491,

Narrator: Despite distancing ourselves from R...
en


Despite distancing ourselves from Rumburg, I feared what consequences her actions would bring to our part of Merkopa.

LineNo: 12544871,

Narrator: While she assured me earlier that s...
en


While she assured me earlier that she didn't intend to go to war, her speech was making headlines in Rizia, questioning our stance in case of a potential conflict.

LineNo: 12544973,

Narrator: I knew she desired war from the beg...
en


I knew she desired war from the beginning. And her unprecedented speech was now making headlines in Rizia, questioning our stance in case of a potential conflict.

LineNo: 12545075,

Narrator: Despite the spectacle, it did not i...
en


Despite the spectacle, it did not interest me in the slightest.

LineNo: 12545177,

Narrator: It was the Merkopan Cup Quarter Fin...
en


It was the Merkopan Cup Quarter Finals. Real Montaklar was playing in Arcasia against the football giants, Olympique Ventrie.

LineNo: 12545279,

en


I stood up and approached the window to take a closer look at the gates.

Menu Text en


Take a closer look.

I didn't pay attention. Instead, I changed the channel.

Keep watching the TV.

LineNo: 12545495,

Narrator: They were rebroadcasting a famous R...
en


They were rebroadcasting a famous Rizian serial, the Adventures of Sir Rezna. The fantastical hero, based on Count Rezna, fought entire tribes and armies of invaders, entirely on his own.

LineNo: 12545597,

Narrator: There was a Rumburgian documentary...
en


There was a Rumburgian documentary about the Bludish Freedom Front. Journalists were interviewing Bludish people from Wehlen, Sordland and Lespia, discussing the pain and suffering of their people in those countries.

LineNo: 12545707,

Player_Romus_Italic: I changed the channel.
en


I changed the channel.

LineNo: 12545713,

Player_Romus_Italic: I changed the channel.
Menu Text en


Change the channel.

LineNo: 12545815,

Player_Romus_Italic: I found the footage interesting, so...
en


I found the footage interesting, so I kept watching.

LineNo: 12545821,

Player_Romus_Italic: I found the footage interesting, so...
Menu Text en


Keep watching.

LineNo: 12545923,

Narrator: The documentary had woven together...
en


The documentary had woven together old clips of Wiktor Smolak giving fiery speeches against the BFF, and grainy footage of former Sordish president Tarquin Soll posing sternly at the cameras.

LineNo: 12546025,

Narrator: Bludish fighters with KA-74s were b...
en


Bludish fighters with KA-74s were being interviewed and praised by Rumburgian journalists, who dubbed them the 'freedom fighters of Eastern Merkopa'.

LineNo: 12546127,

Narrator: Despite the skill with which the fi...
en


Despite the skill with which the film was made, I lost interest in it after a few minutes.

LineNo: 12546229,

Narrator: And at the end of each episode, he...
en


And at the end of each episode, he would singlehandedly save the Rizian people from an otherwise inescapable end.

LineNo: 12546331,

Narrator: I struggled to make out anything in...
en


I struggled to make out anything in the dark. I realized that the entire palace gardens had gone pitch black.

LineNo: 12546433,

Narrator: Suddenly, I noticed a few large sha...
en


Suddenly, I noticed a few large shadows moving from the gates towards the palace at full speed.

LineNo: 12546543,

Player_Romus_Italic: I kept watching the shapes as they...
en


I kept watching the shapes as they got closer.

LineNo: 12546549,

Player_Romus_Italic: I kept watching the shapes as they...
Menu Text en


Keep watching.

LineNo: 12546651,

Player_Romus_Italic: I stepped outside my chambers and a...
en


I stepped outside my chambers and alerted the Wruhec's Guardians.

LineNo: 12546657,

Player_Romus_Italic: I stepped outside my chambers and a...
Menu Text en


Call the guards.

LineNo: 12546759,

Narrator: As I watched the show, I heard the...
en


As I watched the show, I heard the sound of vehicles approaching the palace.

LineNo: 12546869,

Narrator: As soon as they walked in, we heard...
en


As soon as they walked in, we heard the sound of engines roaring. We could now see them clearly.

LineNo: 12546977,

Player_Romus_Italic: I stood up and approached the windo...
en


I stood up and approached the windows to take a closer look.

LineNo: 12546983,

Player_Romus_Italic: I stood up and approached the windo...
Menu Text en


Look at out the window.

LineNo: 12547085,

Player_Romus_Italic: I ignored the noise and kept watchi...
en


I ignored the noise and kept watching the show as Rezna fought his way into Pales.

LineNo: 12547091,

Player_Romus_Italic: I ignored the noise and kept watchi...
Menu Text en


Keep watching the TV.

LineNo: 12547193,

en


They were armored personnel carriers with mounted guns. They surrounded the building and stopped their engines.

LineNo: 12547301,

Narrator: They were armored personnel carrier...
en


They were armored personnel carriers with mounted guns. They surrounded the building and stopped their engines.

LineNo: 12547409,

Narrator: Suddenly, the doors opened and the...
en


Suddenly, the doors opened and the Wruhec's Guardians rushed in. They looked relieved to see me.

LineNo: 12547511,

Narrator: With a sudden thud, the doors opene...
en


With a sudden thud, the doors opened and my guards rushed in. They seemed relieved to see me.

LineNo: 12547613,

Narrator: The guards pointed out the window w...
en


The guards pointed out the window with puzzled looks on their faces, gesturing at the flag on the vehicle below.

LineNo: 12548549,

Narrator: It was the coat of arms of House Az...
en


It was the coat of arms of House Azaro.

Narrator: It was the coat of arms of House To...
en


It was the coat of arms of House Toras.

LineNo: 12548753,

Narrator: It was the coat of arms of House Sa...
en


It was the coat of arms of House Sazon.

LineNo: 12549689,

Narrator: Behind the leading vehicles, I also...
en


Behind the leading vehicles, I also noticed the flags of House Toras and Sazon.

LineNo: 12549791,

Narrator: Behind the leading vehicles, I also...
en


Behind the leading vehicles, I also noticed the flags of House Toras.

LineNo: 12549893,

Narrator: Behind the leading vehicles, I also...
en


Behind the leading vehicles, I also noticed the flags of House Sazon.

LineNo: 12549995,

Narrator: As we were trying to understand wha...
en


As we were trying to understand what was going on, the guards told me their radio was not receiving any signal.

LineNo: 12550097,

Narrator: As we were trying to understand wha...
en


As we were trying to understand what was going on, a few police vehicles from the Porte Drazon Police Department also drove inside the gates.

LineNo: 12550199,

Narrator: Suddenly, the guards told me their...
en


Suddenly, the guards told me their radio was not receiving any signal.

LineNo: 12550421,

Player_Romus: What, the radio doesn't work? Then...
en


"What, the radio doesn't work? Then go and tell the others what's happening! Now!"

Player_Romus: Go and make sure Vina and my mothe...
en


"Go and make sure Vina and my mother are safe."

LineNo: 12550915,

Player_Romus: Go and make sure my mother is safe.
en


"Go and make sure my mother is safe."

LineNo: 12551293,

Player_Romus: Bring Titus here immediately!
en


"Bring Titus here immediately!"

LineNo: 12551401,

Player_Romus: Don't go anywhere. Stay with me.
en


"Don't go anywhere. Stay with me."

LineNo: 12551509,

en


The guards, shouting "Yes, Your Majesty," rushed out my chambers.

LineNo: 12551611,

Narrator: The guards, shouting Yes, Your Maj...
en


The guards, shouting "Yes, Your Majesty," readied their weapons.

en


Just then, a man in full military uniform grabbed a megaphone and made an announcement that echoed through the palace's interior.

en


"Romus Toras. Palas Rezna is completely surrounded."

LineNo: 12552013,

Narrator: Abdicate the throne to Angelica Sa...
en


"Abdicate the throne to Angelica Sazon, and your life and noble status will be spared."

Narrator: She was released from captivity to...
en


"She was released from captivity today, and shall be recognized as the Queen of Rizia."

LineNo: 12553607,

Narrator: Abdicate the throne to Lucita Azar...
en


"Abdicate the throne to Lucita Azaro, and your life and noble status will be spared."

LineNo: 12553987,

Narrator: Abdicate the throne to Taddeus Aza...
en


"Abdicate the throne to Taddeus Azaro, and your life and noble status will be spared."

Narrator: Abdicate the throne to Hugo Toras,...
en


"Abdicate the throne to Hugo Toras, and your life and noble status will be spared."

en


"Abdicate the throne to Ricardus Toras, and your life and noble status will be spared."

LineNo: 12554293,

Narrator: He was released from captivity tod...
en


"He was released from captivity today, and shall be recognized as the true King."

LineNo: 12554875,

Narrator: I repeat. Abdicate and your noble...
en


"I repeat. Abdicate and your noble status will be retained and your House will be respected."

LineNo: 12554977,

Narrator: I repeat. Abdicate and your noble...
en


"I repeat. Abdicate and your noble status will be respected."

LineNo: 12555357,

Narrator: As his words echoed, I felt fear cr...
en


As his words echoed, I felt fear creep up in me.

LineNo: 12555459,

Narrator: The guards looked at me nervously,...
en


The guards looked at me nervously, awaiting orders.

LineNo: 12555855,

Narrator: While she assured me it was the Sor...
en


While she assured me it was the Sords who were readying for war and not Rumburg, I knew that she wanted to attack Sordland from the beginning. And her unprecedented speech was now making headlines in Rizia, questioning our stance in case of a potential conflict.

LineNo: 12555957,

Narrator: Just at that moment, Titus and the...
en


Just at that moment, Titus and the guards rushed in.

en


Just at that moment, my mother and the guards rushed in.

en


"Your Majesty!"

"The entire Golden Guard is in position and ready to defend the palace."

en


"What are your orders?"

LineNo: 12557429,

Estela Toras: Oh, Thank God, you're safe.
en


"Oh, Thank God, you're safe."

LineNo: 12557531,

Estela Toras: Oh, Thank God, you're safe.
en


"Oh, Thank God, you're safe."

en


"Father. Is this really happening?"

en


"Romus. Is this really happening?"

en


"What are you going to do?"

Narrator: Seeing the armored vehicles surroun...
en


Seeing the armored vehicles surrounding the palace, her face turned pale.

LineNo: 12558057,

Player_Romus: I have to talk to them.
en


"I have to talk to them."

"There is nothing I can do. I'm afraid I have to do as they say."

en


"I'm going to fight back. Guards! Get in position and open fire!"

Player_Romus: Good. We will fight back. Tell the...
en


"Good. We will fight back. Tell them to open fire."

LineNo: 12558489,

Player_Romus: I need to do as they say.
en


"I need to do as they say."

LineNo: 12558597,

Player_Romus: I think I have to address them.
en


"I think I have to address them."

LineNo: 12558705,

Player_Romus: We have to fight back. Tell the Go...
en


"We have to fight back. Tell the Golden Guard to open fire. Now!"

Player_Romus: You have to get me and my family o...
en


"You have to get me and my family out of here. Now. I will talk to the soldiers in the meantime."

LineNo: 12558921,

Player_Romus: I don't think we have a chance. I...
en


"I don't think we have a chance. I will do as they say."

LineNo: 12559307,

Player_Romus: We have to fight back. Tell the Wr...
en


"We have to fight back. Tell the Wruhec's Guardians to open fire. Now!"

Narrator: The soldiers saluted me as I grabbe...
en


The soldiers saluted me as I grabbed a coat and walked out on the balcony.

en


"But what are your intentions, Your Majesty?"

LineNo: 12559827,

en


"I don't think we have a chance. I will do as they say."

LineNo: 12559935,

Player_Romus: I don't know yet, Titus. I want yo...
en


"I don't know yet, Titus. I want you to figure out the best course of action while they're focused on me."

LineNo: 12560043,

Player_Romus: I'll save us time by talking to th...
en


"I'll save us time by talking to them. You get everyone in position and open fire when they're focused on me. Do you understand?"

LineNo: 12560151,

Titus Gordion: But...
en


"But..."

LineNo: 12560253,

Titus Gordion: As you wish, Your Majesty.
en


"As you wish, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 12560451,

Narrator: He saluted me while I grabbed a coa...
en


He saluted me while I grabbed a coat and walked out on the balcony.

LineNo: 12560553,

Narrator: Before they could say anything, I g...
en


Before they could say anything, I grabbed a coat and walked out on the balcony.

Estela Toras: No, Romus. You can't!
en


"No, Romus. You can't!"

LineNo: 12561051,

Player_Romus: I'll save us time by talking to th...
en


"I'll save us time by talking to them. In the meantime find Titus and tell him to get everyone in position and open fire when they're focused on me. Do you understand?"

Player_Romus: I have to do this to save our fami...
en


"I have to do this to save our family."

en


"Don't worry. I'll be right back."

LineNo: 12561375,

Player_Romus: I'll save us time by talking to th...
en


"I'll save us time by talking to them. Just find the guards and try to escape the palace. Do you understand?"

en


When the officers outside saw me on the balcony, they looked at me with a mixture of disbelief and relief.

en


The officer who made the announcement spoke to me, this time without the use of his megaphone: "Tell your men to surrender their weapons."

Player_Romus: Listen to me now. You're going to...
en


"Listen to me now. You're going to take your weapons and leave my palace and *I* will forget this happened. You still have a chance to back off."

Player_Romus: Where the hell is my cousin? You'r...
en


"Where the hell is my cousin? You're doing the bidding of a man who doesn't even have the guts to face me himself."

LineNo: 12563159,

Player_Romus: Where the hell is my uncle? You're...
en


"Where the hell is my uncle? You're doing the bidding of a man who doesn't even have the guts to face me himself."

LineNo: 12563267,

Player_Romus: Where the hell is Lucita? You're d...
en


"Where the hell is Lucita? You're doing the bidding of a woman who doesn't even have the guts to face me herself."

LineNo: 12563375,

Player_Romus: Where the hell is Taddeus? You're...
en


"Where the hell is Taddeus? You're doing the bidding of an old man who doesn't even have the guts to face me himself."

LineNo: 12563483,

Player_Romus: Where the hell is Angelica? You're...
en


"Where the hell is Angelica? You're doing the bidding of a woman who doesn't even have the guts to face me herself."

LineNo: 12563591,

Player_Romus: I am here to talk.
en


"I am here to talk."

LineNo: 12563699,

Player_Romus: I'm not fighting back.
en


"I'm not fighting back."

LineNo: 12563807,

Player_Romus_Italic: I stood there and stared at them fr...
en


I stood there and stared at them from the balcony.

Don't say anything.

LineNo: 12564049,

en


None of the soldiers reacted.

LineNo: 12564151,

Player_Romus: Am I not standing here in front of...
en


"Am I not standing here in front of hundreds of weapons?"

LineNo: 12564259,

Player_Romus: I will.
en


"I will."

LineNo: 12564367,

Player_Romus: I know when the cards are stacked...
en


"I know when the cards are stacked against me."

LineNo: 12564475,

Player_Romus: Why are you doing this?
en


"Why are you doing this?"

LineNo: 12564583,

Player_Romus: As the King of Rizia, I need *you*...
en


"As the King of Rizia, I need *you* to cooperate with me here."

LineNo: 12564691,

en


The officer was not amused. He shouted at me with a dismissive tone: "Tell your men to surrender their weapons."

LineNo: 12564809,

Narrator: We must now enter the palace. Do w...
en


"We must now enter the palace. Do we have your word of your cooperation?"

LineNo: 12564935,

Player_Romus: Why?
en


"Why?"

LineNo: 12565043,

Player_Romus: I need you all to stay exactly whe...
en


"I need you all to stay exactly where you are."

LineNo: 12565151,

Player_Romus: Yes. You have my word.
en


"Yes. You have my word."

LineNo: 12565259,

Player_Romus: If you walk one step closer to the...
en


"If you walk one step closer to the palace, my guards will open fire."

LineNo: 12565367,

Narrator: He left his vehicle with a group of...
en


He left his vehicle with a group of soldiers and started walking to the door, as rest of the soldiers pointed their guns at the building.

LineNo: 12565469,

Player_Romus: You heard him. Surrender your weap...
en


"You heard him. Surrender your weapons now!"

LineNo: 12565577,

Player_Romus: I cannot do that.
en


"I cannot do that."

LineNo: 12565685,

Player_Romus: Why don't you surrender your weapo...
en


"Why don't you surrender your weapons before it's too late?"

LineNo: 12566071,

Narrator: He pointed his gun at me.
en


He pointed his gun at me.

LineNo: 12566189,

Narrator: As the guards in the palace dropped...
en


As the guards in the palace dropped their weapons, the rebels entered the palace.

LineNo: 12566291,

Narrator: Just then, the stable doors burst o...
en


Just then, the stable doors burst open with a resounding thud, and two royal horses bolted through the palace gardens.

LineNo: 12566393,

Player_Romus: Soldier! You're pointing your weap...
en


"Soldier! You're pointing your weapon to a King! Your King! Lower that gun immediately!"

LineNo: 12566501,

Player_Romus: Go ahead. Shoot me then. I am not...
en


"Go ahead. Shoot me then. I am not going to cooperate."

LineNo: 12566609,

Narrator: As several soldiers turned their he...
en


As several soldiers turned their heads around in panic, a thick cloud of smoke engulfed the courtyard, followed by an ear-splitting explosion. I watched in horror as the officer's vehicle was torn apart, splattering the cobbles with blood and metal.

LineNo: 12566711,

Narrator: I hurled myself back inside as guns...
en


I hurled myself back inside as gunshots erupted from all directions.

LineNo: 12567091,

Narrator: The officer was not right below the...
en


The officer was not right below the balcony, he spoke to me in a much lower voice: "Please tell your men to surrender their weapons, sir."

LineNo: 12567209,

Narrator: Tell your men to surrender their w...
en


"Tell your men to surrender their weapons. Now."

LineNo: 12567327,

Player_Romus: Guards! Listen to him!
en


"Guards! Listen to him!"

LineNo: 12567435,

Player_Romus: Guards! Open fire!
en


"Guards! Open fire!"

LineNo: 12567543,

Titus Gordion: As you wish, Your Majesty.
en


"As you wish, Your Majesty."

LineNo: 12567645,

Titus Gordion: But before I can do that, I must t...
en


"But before I can do that, I must take you to a safe location."

en


The guards insisted on taking me to a safe room before initiating the attack.

LineNo: 12568143,

Vina Toras: What? No!
en


"What? No!"

LineNo: 12568245,

Estela Toras: What? No!
en


"What? No!"

en


"We have no time. Open fire immediately!"

Follow them to the safe room.

en


"We have no time. Open fire immediately!"

en


I followed him to the safe room.

Player_Romus_Italic: I followed him to the safe room.

Follow him to the safe room.

en


He nodded and gave a signal through his radio.

en

en


Just then, with a deafening noise, the palace guards started firing at the soldiers below.

Narrator: I threw myself to the ground as an...
en


I threw myself to the ground as an ear-splitting explosion engulfed the courtyard.

LineNo: 12569391,

Narrator: Hearing my screams, the guards open...
en


Hearing my screams, the guards opened fire below.

LineNo: 12569595,

Narrator: As we walked through the corridors...
en


As we walked through the corridors and went downstairs, I heard gunshots being exchanged outside.

LineNo: 12570071,

Narrator: My mother looked at me in shock as...
en


My mother looked at me in shock as gunshots were fired from each direction.

Narrator: Titus grabbed me from my arm and dr...
en


Titus grabbed me from my arm and dragged me to the corridors.

LineNo: 12570275,

Vina Toras: Father! What do we do?
en


"Father! What do we do?"

LineNo: 12570671,

Estela Toras: Romus! What do we do?
en


"Romus! What do we do?"

LineNo: 12570789,

en


The guards grabbed me from my arm and dragged me to the corridors.

LineNo: 12570891,

Narrator: As we navigated through the hidden...
en


As we navigated through the hidden passages down below, the noises of the battle diminished.

LineNo: 12570999,

Narrator: We then went downstairs, as we hear...
en


We then went downstairs, as we heard gunshots being exchanged outside.

LineNo: 12571107,

Narrator: This room was a stark contrast to t...
en


This room was a stark contrast to the opulence of the palace – a simple, fortified space devoid of any luxury, designed solely for survival.

LineNo: 12571215,
